<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-02-05T23:34:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-02-05T23:34:00-05:00" n="694" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d694">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2410: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Harbin</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Jenkins</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-02-06T13:00:00+08:26"><hi rend="italic">February 6,
                                        1922—1 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received February 6—12:17
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Chinese have organized society here to carry on campaign against
                            international control Chinese Eastern Railway. Street demonstration took
                            place yesterday. Movement believed to be instigated by order of the
                            authorities. Legation informed.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Jenkins</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>